        "data": "<b>2. Steps to Write a Summary</b>\n1. Read the passage carefully and understand it fully.\n2. Identify the main idea of each paragraph.\n3. Note important supporting details that clarify or explain the main ideas.\n4. Eliminate examples, repetitions, and unimportant details.\n5. Write in your own words, maintaining logical sequence and coherence.\n6. Keep it concise; the summary is usually 1/3 or less of the original passage length."
