        "data": "<b>Model Answer:</b>\nMy favourite place is the serene and picturesque garden near my house. It is a haven of peace and beauty, where I often go to relax, read, or simply enjoy nature. From the entrance, one is greeted by a pathway lined with flowering plants in vibrant colors—red, yellow, purple, and white. The flowers sway gently in the breeze, releasing a delicate fragrance that instantly calms the mind.\n\nAs I walk further into the garden, I notice a small pond at the center. The water is crystal clear, reflecting the blue sky above and the green trees surrounding it. Ducks swim gracefully on the pond, occasionally diving beneath the surface, creating ripples that shimmer under the sunlight. Near the pond, benches are strategically placed, offering visitors a perfect spot to sit and admire the beauty around them.\n\nTall trees with thick, leafy branches provide shade along the winding paths. Birds sing harmoniously from their nests, filling the air with melodious tunes. I often see squirrels darting up and down the trees, adding life and energy to the peaceful environment. The sound of leaves rustling in the wind and the distant hum of bees visiting flowers create a symphony that is both soothing and uplifting.\n\nThe garden is well-maintained, with neatly trimmed hedges and clean walkways. Seasonal flowers are planted in specific patterns, creating a tapestry of colors that change throughout the year. In the evenings, the soft golden light of the setting sun bathes the garden in warmth, making it even more enchanting. It is during these moments that I feel a deep sense of contentment and reflection.\n\nMy favourite place is not only beautiful but also has a special meaning for me. It is a place where I can think clearly, away from the noise and distractions of daily life. Whenever I feel stressed or overwhelmed, a visit to this garden restores my energy and inspires creativity. I often bring my notebook and pen to jot down ideas or write poetry, as the tranquil surroundings stimulate my imagination.\n\nIn conclusion, this garden is my sanctuary. Its vibrant flowers, serene pond, melodious birds, and shady trees make it a perfect escape from the pressures of life. Spending time there brings joy, peace, and inspiration, and it is a place I will always cherish. The garden teaches me to appreciate the beauty of nature and find calmness amidst life’s challenges."
