        "data": "<b>Definition of Poetry:</b>\nPoetry is a form of literature that expresses ideas, emotions, and experiences through carefully selected words, arranged in lines and stanzas. It uses rhythm, imagery, and figurative language to create memorable effects. WAEC and JAMB test poetry through analysis of themes, tone, structure, poetic devices, and interpretation."
